	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />k, n00b here, but,
<br />
<br />thinking of trying out the Famicom disk system emulator, without the drive, but on an american NES. The idea is to load rom onto some RAM adapter from pc and play on console, BUT
<br />
<br />the disk system doens't seem to have been built for the american one. if the ram adapter is "adapted" into the american NES should it work? has anyone every tried this? 
<br />
<br />also, are there any schems for a ram adapted that i can build? Rram adapters have been hard to find, and also, space is a concern, so if i can make it small it would be worth it.
<br />
<br />
<br />and... has anyone else tried the famicom disk  emulator idea?
<br />
<br />loky

		

		</td>
	</tr>
