	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">loky wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">the disk system doens't seem to have been built for the american one. if the ram adapter is "adapted" into the american NES should it work? has anyone every tried this?</div><br />I seem to remember that someone got it to work with a Gyromite adapter and a Game Genie.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">also, are there any schems for a ram adapted that i can build?</div>
<br />The "RAM adapter" also contains the mapper circuitry, which generates IRQs and handles the disk signals and the like. Unless you are handy with an FPGA and VHDL, I wouldn't recommend it.

		

